==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sandarac
<hw>San"da*rac</hw>, }</mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sandaraca</ets>, Gr.
<?/.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Realgar; red sulphide of
arsenic.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. Chem.)</fld> <def>A white or yellow resin
obtained from a Barbary tree (<spn>Callitris quadrivalvis</spn> or
<spn>Thuya articulata</spn>), and pulverized for pounce; -- probably so
called from a resemblance to the mineral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>sandbag</ent>⟦br⟧
